'''''Lost in the Garden''''' is a [[Midlife crisis|midlife-crisis]] novel by the American writer [[Philip Beard]].<ref>{{cite journal | title = ''Philip Beard'', '''Contemporary Authors Online''', Detroit: Thomson Gale, 2008}}</ref>
Set in contemporary [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania]], it tells the story of 45-year-old Michael Benedict, who after the failure of his marriage, moves back with his parents and sets himself a goal of breaking 70 in his golf game and making the [[Champions Tour]] by age 50.<ref>{{cite journal | title = ''Lost in the Garden'' (2006), '''Publishers Weekly''', 2006}}</ref>
