{{Infobox government agency | agency_name = Ministry of Culture, Tourism and Civil Aviation | type = | nativename = संस्कृति, पर्यटन तथा नागरिक उड्डयन मन्त्रालय | nativename_a = | nativename_r = | logo = Emblem of Nepal.svg | logo_width = 100 | logo_caption = | seal = | seal_width = | seal_caption = | picture = | picture_width = | picture_caption = | formed = 1978 | preceding1 = | preceding2 = <!-- (etc.) --> | dissolved = | superseding = | jurisdiction = {{flag|Nepal|2015}} | headquarters = [[Singha Durbar]], Kathmandu | coordinates = <!--{{coord|LATITUDE|LONGITUDE|type:landmark_region:US|display=inline,title}}--> | motto = | employees = | budget = | minister1_name = [[Rabindra Prasad Adhikari]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.myrepublica.com/news/38157/?categoryId=81 |title=PM inducts 15 members to cabinet |website=My Republica |language=en |access-date=2018-03-19}}</ref> | minister_pfo = | minister2_name = | minister2_pfo = <!-- (etc.) --> | deputyminister1_name = | deputyminister1_pfo = | deputyminister2_name = | deputyminister2_pfo = <!-- (etc.) --> | chief1_name = Ghanshyam Upadhyaya | chief1_position = Joint Secretary | chief2_name = Suresh Acharya | chief2_position = Joint Secretary <!-- (etc.) --> | agency_type = | parent_department = | parent_agency = | child1_agency = | child2_agency = <!-- (etc.) --> | keydocument1 = <!-- (etc.) --> | website = {{URL|tourism.gov.np}} | footnotes = | map = | map_width = | map_caption = }}
The '''Ministry of Culture, Tourism and Civil Aviation''' is the [[Government of Nepal|governmental body]] for promoting [[Tourism in Nepal|tourism]], [[Culture of Nepal|culture]] and private sector involvement in [[Nepal]]. It also serves as the Nepalese aviation regulatory body. The ministry is located in Singha Durbar, Kathmandu. {{As of|March 2018}}, the ministry is currently led by [[Rabindra Prasad Adhikari]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tourism.gov.np/ |title=संस्कृति, पर्यटन तथा नागरिक उड्डयन मन्त्रालय |website=www.tourism.gov.np |language=en |access-date=2018-03-19}}</ref>
==History== The '''Ministry of Tourism''' was established in 1978 by the [[Government of Nepal]]. The portfolios of Civil Aviation and Culture were added in 1982 and 2000 respectively. This structure was dissolved again in 2008, when the ministry was split into the Ministry of Tourism and Civil Aviation on the one side and the Ministry of Culture and State Restructuring on the other side. In 2012, the ministry was again renamed and gained its current form as the Ministry of Culture, Tourism and Civil Aviation.<ref>{{cite web|title=हाम्रो बारेमा|url=http://www.tourism.gov.np/ne/content.php?id=2|publisher=Government of Nepal|accessdate=1 April 2018|language=Nepali}}</ref>
==Organisational Structure== The Ministry of Culture, Tourism and Civil Aviation has several departments and subdivisions:<ref>{{cite web|title=हाम्रो बारेमा|url=http://www.tourism.gov.np/ne/content.php?id=35|publisher=Ministry of Culture, Tourism and Civil Aviation|accessdate=27 October 2017|language=Nepali}}</ref> * [[Civil Aviation Authority of Nepal]] * [[Department of Archaeology (Nepal)|Department of Archaeology]] * [[Nepal Airlines|Nepal Airlines Corporation]] * [[National Lake Conservation Development Committee]] * Aviation Security Division * Department of Tourism * Nepal Academy of Tourism and Hotel Management (NATHM) * Nepal Tourism Board
